<div metal:use-macro="container/macro_edit_view/macros/edit_view">

<div metal:fill-slot="edit_input" tal:omit-tag="">
&nbsp;List title:<br />
<textarea name="list_title" cols="65" rows="2" style="font-weight:bold;" size="65" value=""
  tal:content="python:here.util.get_title_text(node)">Title</textarea><br /><br />

<input type="button" class="button" name="" value="Append asset reference" style="float:right;" title="Access key: Alt-a" accesskey="a"
  tal:attributes="onclick python:'getAssetReference(\'%s/edit/asset_lookup\', \'((_id_|_reference_))\', \'focusbox\', \'data\', 1);;return false;;' % node.get_container().absolute_url()" />
&nbsp;List items: <br style="clear:both;" /> 
<script type="text/javascript" tal:content="structure here/asset_reference.js" />
<script type="text/javascript" tal:content="structure python:here.focus_editor('data')" />
<textarea id="data" name="data" cols="65" rows="12" tal:attributes="rows here/get_lines"
  tal:content="here/editable_content">Dummy</textarea><br />
</div>

<div metal:fill-slot="element_controls" tal:omit-tag="">
<script type="text/javascript" tal:content="structure here/elements.js" />
Element: 
<select name="what" onChange="updateSelectionOptions()">
  <option value="p">paragraph</option>
  <option value="pre">preformatted</option>
  <option value="heading">heading</option>
  <option value="list">list</option>
  <option value="dlist" selected="selected">definition list</option>
  <option value="nlist" tal:replace="nothing">complex list</option>
</select>
&nbsp;&nbsp;
<check tal:condition="python:node.hasAttribute('type')" tal:omit-tag="">
<init tal:define="global type python:node.getAttribute('type')" tal:omit-tag="" />
</check>
<check tal:condition="python:not node.hasAttribute('type')" tal:omit-tag="">
<init tal:define="global type nothing" tal:omit-tag="" />
</check>
Type: 
<select name="element_type">
<option value="normal"
  tal:attributes="selected python:test(type == 'normal', 'selected', nothing)">normal</option>
<option value="compact"
  tal:attributes="selected python:test(type == 'compact', 'selected', nothing)">compact</option>
</select>

</div>

<div metal:fill-slot="edit_notes" tal:omit-tag="">
<ul class="tips">
  <li>Add definition term on first line, definition on second line, separate items with an empty line space.</li>
  <li><b>Tip:</b> Tab to the exit button or use alt-e.</li>
  <li>Text can be formatted &#8211; in <i>italic</i>, <b>bold</b>, etc. &#8211; with &#8220;Silva markup&#8221;:
    <ul class="tips-nested">
      <li>**bold** ++italic++ __underlined__ ^^superscript^^ ~~subscript~~</li>
      <li>((link text|http://www.x.yz))</li>
      <li>((link text|http://www.x.yz|target)) &#8212; if &#8216;target&#8217; is empty a new window opens</li>
      <li>[[index item|item as shown in index]]</li>
      <li tal:replace="nothing">{{name of person|name in index}}</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
